The article discusses a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on Columbus Day. It recognizes Christopher Columbus's historic voyage to the Americas and the impact it had on shaping human history. The proclamation honors Columbus as a skilled navigator and man of faith who inspired others to pursue their dreams. It also acknowledges the contributions of Italian Americans to the United States and reaffirms the close ties between the US and Italy. The proclamation calls for observing Columbus Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities and for displaying the US flag on public buildings.